'''Shikinai Shrine List of Mikawa Province''' (三河国の式内社一覧) is a list of the shrines (so‑called {{ill|Shikinai Shrines|de|Shikinai-Schreine|ja|式内社|zh|式内社|12=draft}}) recorded under Mikawa Province in volumes 9–10 of the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|de|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|zh|延喜式神名帳|12=draft}}. Shrines existing at time of compilation but not listed (so‑called {{ill|Shikige Shrines|de|Shikige-Schreine|ja|式外社|zh|式外社|12=draft}}) are noted separately.
-->

This is a '''List of Shikinaisha in Mikawa Province'''. Or the list of shrines in [[Mikawa Province]] which is present in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|12=draft}}. On this page we will also cover the {{ill|Shikigeisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|12=draft}} of [[Mikawa Province]] which are shrines that are known to have existed at that time due to other historical records, such as the [[Rikkokushi]], but for some reason were excluded from the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|12=draft}}. We will cover them in a separate list to avoid confusion.
== Shikinai Shrines (式内社) == The Engishiki Jinmyōchō lists 26 seats (25 distinct shrines) of the minor Rank.
